abstract: A Senate subcommittee told JPMorgan Chase to immediately start turning over a year’s worth of internal documents about the bank’s view on oil speculation.

abstract: A Senate subcommittee told JPMorgan Chase on Wednesday to immediately start turning over a year’s worth of internal documents about the bank’s view on oil speculation, according to The New York Times’s Diana B. Henriques.
